data.title: Roy the Champ
data.prompt: Create a song about the olympic boxing gold medalist named roy jones
data.tags: driving rhythm, bold instrumentation with punchy percussion and electric guitars
data.lyrics:
[Verse]
Gloves up high in the smoky haze
Golden fists
They set the world ablaze
Dancing like a shadow
Floating on air
Roy's in the ring
No one else compares

[Prechorus]
They threw their best
He threw it better
Knocked 'em down like a love letter

[Chorus]
Roy Jones
The champ
The king of the fight
Quick as lightning
Burning so bright
They swung
He swayed
They missed
He stayed
Roy Jones
Gold medal made

[Verse 2]
Steps so slick
Like a ghost in the night
Dodging punches
Turning wrong to right
Eyes on the prize
No time for fear
A roar in the crowd
"Roy is here!"

[Prechorus]
He danced
They fell
The bell would sing
The crown belongs to the boxing king

[Chorus]
Roy Jones
The champ
The king of the fight
Quick as lightning
Burning so bright
They swung
He swayed
They missed
He stayed
Roy Jones
Gold medal made
